Spec: SpecDD Language Metadata

Purpose:
  Provide shared constants and section metadata used by parser, providers, completions, and hovers.

Owns:
  ./language.ts

Can read:
  ../reference/LANGUAGE.md

Must:
  Keep canonical section labels, supported task markers, scenario keywords, and section descriptions aligned with the language reference.
  Expose metadata as simple typed constants with no filesystem or VS Code dependencies.
  Preserve section label spelling and case exactly as defined by the language reference.

Must not:
  Add behavior that belongs in the parser, reference resolver, or VS Code extension layer.
